channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Migrants Seeking Safety in Cyprus Are Stuck in U.N. Buffer Zone
item.description: Nearly 30 people who hoped to seek refuge in the European Union nation are in limbo after trying to cross from the Turkish-occupied part of the island. Many are Syrians who left Lebanon.

item.title: Middle East Crisis: Israel and Hamas Signal Openness to Cease-Fire Plan, but Stop Short of Accepting It
item.description: The fate of a U.S.-backed cease-fire proposal remained unclear a day after the U.N. Security Council endorsed it in a unanimous vote.

item.title: Canadian youth have put hockey on thin ice: As participation declines, the future on the beloved pastime is precarious
item.description: Hockey Canada reported a 35% drop in youth hockey participation compared to 13 years ago.

item.title: Age Limit for Congressional Candidates Is on North Dakota’s 2024 Ballot
item.description: A vote on Tuesday on a proposed age limit for members of Congress is a rare chance to find out what voters actually believe about politicians and age.

item.title: 'The world might become stuck in the slow lane'—World Bank warns of the consequences of sustaining elevated interest rates
item.description: "We need to avoid lower-for-longer economic growth around the world," said The World Bank's deputy chief economist Ayhan Kose.

item.title: The Gay-Bashing Email Splitting Colorado’s Republican Party
item.description: The MAGA movement tears another state Republican Party apart.

item.title: Here’s a Look at the U.N.-Endorsed Cease-Fire Proposal for Gaza
item.description: The Security Council can’t force anyone to adopt the plan, but its passage of a resolution backing it increases pressure on both sides to make a deal.

item.title: Ambition Mastercard® review: Build credit in college on your terms
item.description: The Ambition Mastercard® is a hybrid secured card with no credit check and a flexible deposit.

item.title: The Vaquita Porpoise Still Exists. Here’s the Latest Count.
item.description: Scientists and officials spent days at sea searching for vaquitas, shy porpoises threatened by fishing gear.

item.title: No, a Remote Amazon Tribe Did Not Get Addicted to Porn
item.description: A Times story about the arrival of high-speed internet in a remote Amazon tribe spiraled into its own cautionary tale on the dark side of the web.

item.title: No one wants another pandemic—but bird flu has already flown the coop
item.description: The H5N1 virus, also known as bird flu or avian influenza, is surging among mammals and proving itself very versatile at jumping from species to species.

item.title: A Candidate Got $162,000 in Public Money. His Secret: Fake Donors.
item.description: New York’s new matching-funds campaign system rewards candidates who raise money from small donors, but weak oversight may already have led to abuses.

item.title: France in Shock as Conservative Leader Embraces Far Right
item.description: The announcement by the head of the Republicans was a historic break with his party’s policy as dismay spread over a snap election.

item.title: Hunter Biden convicted of all 3 felony charges in federal gun trial
item.description: President Biden's son was found guilty of lying to a gun dealer, making a false claim on the application, and illegally having the gun for 11 days.
